article.headline: N. Illinois 85, Duquesne 74
article.story: DEKALB, Ill. (AP) -- James Hughes had a team-high 22 points to lead Northern Illinois to a 85-74 victory over Duquesne on Saturday, the Huskies' second straight victory in as many games over the Dukes. Hughes added a game-high 10 rebounds for the Huskies (3-0), who also beat Duquesne 87-82 in overtime in Pittsburgh on Monday. Northern Illinois had four players in double figures. Zack Pancratz had 16 points, Ryan Paradise added 11 and Mike McKinney chipped in 10 points for the Huskies, who led 46-37 at halftime. Robert Mitchell had a game-high 23 points, Scott Grote had 20 points and Aaron Jackson added 11 points for Duquesne (2-3), which shot 8-of-27 from 3-point range. The rematch was the first time in 38 years Duquesne had played a non-league team twice in the same regular season.
